-- return_rate_by_category.sql
SELECT 
    COALESCE(c.name, 'Uncategorized') AS category_name,
    COUNT(oi.item_id) AS total_items_sold,
    COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN r.return_id IS NOT NULL THEN oi.item_id END) AS total_items_returned,
    ROUND(
        COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN r.return_id IS NOT NULL THEN oi.item_id END)::NUMERIC / 
        COUNT(oi.item_id),
        4
    ) AS return_rate
FROM order_items oi
JOIN orders o ON oi.order_id = o.order_id
LEFT JOIN products p ON oi.product_id = p.product_id
LEFT JOIN categories c ON p.category_id = c.category_id
LEFT JOIN returns r ON oi.item_id = r.item_id AND r.status = 'approved'
WHERE o.status IN ('completed', 'shipped', 'delivered')
GROUP BY COALESCE(c.name, 'Uncategorized')
ORDER BY return_rate DESC;
